com.camerontec.catalys.core.session

Interface IParty

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Party

    public interface IParty
extends Serializable
    This represents a party capable of sending and receiving over a FIX Session.

    A FIX Session involves communication between two parties.

    In addition to implementing the methods in this interface, each IParty class should provide a constructor which takes a single Properties object as a parameter.

    For example, 

        MyParty( Properties properties );
    This constructor is used create IParty objects from configuration data.

    The default implementation of IParty (which you probably will not need to change) is Party

    Author:
    John Cameron

    • Method Detail

      • isDescendent

        boolean isDescendent(IParty parent)
        True if this party is a descendant of the given party.

        A descendant has the same fields as its parent, plus some other fields which further define the party.

        For example, a party with compID "A" and subID "B" is a descendant of the party with just compID "A".

        Parameters:
        parent - Party that this party may be a descendant of.
        Returns:
        True if this party is a descendant of given potential parent party.

      • toFileString

        String toFileString()
        Returns a unique String for this Party in a format suitable for use as a file name.

        This is useful if you are storing party related information in files.

        In particular the returned String should not contain any of the following characters... :,=*?/\'"

        If you avoid the above characters, the String should also work as a valid JMX name.

        Returns:
        Party's File String value
